OperatorInfo.Title: Ecotricity
OperatorInfo.Comments: Pay-as-you-go, app-based charging, mostly at Motorway Services in the UK

UserComments.Comment: Site is in the process of being upgraded. All off at the moment. CCS available on nearby ionity
two vehicles queueing for three charge points

UserComments.Comment: long queue for only ccs unit
Chademo charged ok, CCS unit faulty
Charged alongside an Outlander and an i3.
Very busy, all three charge points working.
Two out of three chargers broken (card error / unfinished AC charge). Long queue.
ZOE

CommentType.Title: Fault Report (Notice To Users And Operator)

UserComments.Comment: Right hand unit CCS error, and Chademo can bus not receiving error; Left hand unit was occupied by a BYD taxi (on the dashboard, it was claiming it would take 1 hour and 23 minutes to charge and was at 32% SOC).

Ecotricity reporting on twitter that both units are now online
One machine not working, other one had emergency stop button pushed in, released it and recovered machine, then all good
Charger closed due to fire.
